it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery.actionlisteners

Class CustomizableActionListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery.actionlisteners.CustomizableActionListener

  • public class CustomizableActionListener
extends java.lang.Object
    Extremely customizable WifiP2pManager.ActionListener. The only parameter of the constructor the can't be null, is context. If tag==null, this class chooses a default tag "ActionListenerTag".

    For example, if successToast==null, the Toasts in onSuccess will never displayed.

    Created by Stefano Cappa on 18/02/15.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CustomizableActionListener

        public CustomizableActionListener(Context context,
                                  java.lang.String tag,
                                  java.lang.String successLog,
                                  java.lang.String successToast,
                                  java.lang.String failLog,
                                  java.lang.String failToast)
        Constructor of CustomizableActionListener. successLog, successToast, failLog, failToast can be == null, and if this happens the associated action is skipped.
        Parameters:
        context - Context necessary to display Toasts.
        tag - String that represents the tag for Log.d, but if is == null, this constructor uses "ActionListenerTag" as tag.
        successLog - String that represent the message for Log.d in onSuccess
        successToast - String that represent the message for Toasts in onSuccess
        failLog - String that represent the message for Log.d in onFailure. The failure code will be added automatically.
        failToast - String that represent the message for Toasts in onFailure
